A former commercial administrative manager at Mobil Nigeria Limited, Pa Jeremiah Ahonaruogho, has died at the age of 84. In a statement by Prince Richard Oma Ahonaruogho, SAN, for and on behalf of the Ahonaruogho family, on Friday, the former “Odionwere of Idusogie Eweka Street and Environ Community Association in Benin City, Edo State,” passed away on January 31. According to the statement, the deceased would be buried on February 25, 2022, after a service of songs to be held at his church, Our Saviour’s Anglican Church, Etete, GRA, Benin City, on February 24, 2022. Born on November 23, 1937, Pa Jeremiah Ahonaruogho, who hailed from Ughoton town in the Okpe Local Government Area of Delta State, was educated at the Sheffield College of Technology (now Sheffield Hallam University) from1966 to 1967, where he was awarded a postgraduate diploma certificate in Management Studies He worked as an accounting officer to D.H. Lawson and Company Limited London. He held various management and executive positions, including resale manager, real estate manager and eastern branch manager, at Mobil Oil. The statement added, “Daddy’s contemporary at Mobil Oil included Chief Pius Akinyelure who was at the time Head of Finance under whom was Mr Bola Tinubu (as he then was). Daddy is survived by his wife, Mrs Josephine Ahonaruogho; children, grandchildren, nephews, nieces, and in-laws: the Ojelades from Abeokuta, Ogun State; the Olashores from Iloko Ijesha, Osun State; the Adefolajus from Esa-Oke, Osun State, and the Unigwes from Umudike-Ukpor, Anambra State.”